  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "Vodafone (now Vodafone Idea or Vi in India) offers several ways to check your last 3 charges. Here's a breakdown of the common methods:\n\n**1. Vi App (Easiest Method):**\n\n*   **Download & Install:** If you don't have it, download the \"Vi App\" from the Google Play Store (Android) or App Store (iOS).\n*   **Login:** Log in with your Vodafone Idea (Vi) mobile number.  You might need to verify via OTP.\n*   **Navigate to Usage or Bill Details:** Look for sections like \"Usage,\" \"Data Usage,\" \"Bill Details,\" or \"Recent Transactions.\"  The exact name can vary slightly.\n*   **View Recent Transactions:** Within the usage/bill details, you should find a list of your recent transactions or charges. You may need to specify a date range to narrow it down to the last 3.\n\n**2. USSD Codes (Quick but Limited):**\n\n*   **Dial *111#:**  Dial this code from your Vodafone Idea (Vi) mobile number.\n*   **Follow the Prompts:**  A menu will appear. Look for options related to \"Balance,\" \"Usage,\" or \"Last Recharge.\" Follow the prompts on the screen.  Some USSD menus allow you to specifically check recent transactions.\n*   **Dial *199#:** A menu will pop up which may contain your balance and validity. Look for options to check usage or recent transactions\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Mobile Number:** Make sure you are using the Vodafone Idea (Vi) number you want to check the charges for.\n*   **Data Charges:** Using the Vi App requires a data connection.\n*   **USSD Code Changes:** Mobile operators sometimes change USSD codes, so if *111# or *199# doesn't work, check the Vi website or contact customer care for the updated codes.\n*   **Customer Care:** If none of these methods work, the best option is to contact Vodafone Idea (Vi) customer care.\n\n**Contacting Customer Care:**\n\n*   **Call 199:** Dial 199 from your Vodafone Idea (Vi) mobile number. Follow the prompts to speak to a customer care representative.\n*   **Visit the Vi Website:**  Go to the Vodafone Idea (Vi) website and look for the \"Contact Us\" or \"Support\" section. You may find options for live chat or email support.\n\n**Tips for Better Tracking:**\n\n*   **Regularly Check:** Make it a habit to check your balance and usage periodically.\n*   **Set Data Limits:** Within the Vi app you can set data usage limits to avoid unexpected charges.\n*   **Be Aware of Subscriptions:** Keep track of any value-added services (VAS) you are subscribed to, as they often have recurring charges.\n\nBy using the Vi app, USSD codes, or contacting customer care, you should be able to easily check your last 3 charges and manage your account effectively. Remember that Vodafone is now Vi (Vodafone Idea) in India.\n",
